# English Development Standard

All development code must be written in English, while user-facing text remains in Portuguese.

## Code Elements (English Only)

- **File names**: `problem-section.css`, `header.css`, `userService.js`
- **Variable names**: `userName`, `totalPrice`, `isActive`
- **Function names**: `calculateTotal()`, `fetchUserData()`, `handleClick()`
- **Class names (CSS/HTML)**: `.problem-card`, `.hero-content`, `.btn-primary`
- **IDs**: `#mainContent`, `#userProfile`
- **Comments**: All code comments must be in English
- **Constants**: `MAX_RETRIES`, `API_ENDPOINT`
- **Type definitions**: `interface UserData`, `type OrderStatus`

## User-Facing Content (Portuguese)

- **HTML text content**: Titles, paragraphs, buttons text
- **Alt text for images**: Descriptions for accessibility
- **Placeholder text**: Form inputs and textareas
- **Error messages**: Messages shown to users
- **Success notifications**: User feedback messages

## Examples

### ✅ GOOD

```html
<!-- Class names in English, text content in Portuguese -->
<div class="problem-card">
  <h3 class="card-title">Fornecedores que não estão no digital</h3>
  <button class="btn-primary">Quero saber mais</button>
</div>
```

```css
/* Class names and properties in English */
.problem-section {
  background-color: #ffffff;
  padding: 20px;
}

.card-title {
  font-size: 24px;
  color: #1a1a1a;
}
```

```javascript
// Variables and functions in English, user messages in Portuguese
function fetchSupplierData(supplierId) {
  if (!supplierId) {
    return { error: "ID do fornecedor não encontrado" };
  }
  // Implementation
}
```

### ❌ BAD

```html
<!-- Class names in Portuguese -->
<div class="problema-card">
  <h3 class="titulo-cartao">Title</h3>
  <button class="botao-primario">Click</button>
</div>
```

```css
/* Class names in Portuguese */
.secao-problema {
  cor-de-fundo: #ffffff;
}
```

```javascript
// Variables in Portuguese
function buscarDadosFornecedor(idFornecedor) {
  // Implementation
}
```

## File Naming Convention

- Use kebab-case for HTML/CSS files: `problem-section.css`, `hero-header.html`
- Use camelCase for JavaScript files: `userService.js`, `apiHandler.js`
- Always use English words
